{% block content %}

<h1 class="Article-title">Site</h1>
<p class="Text--lead">Provides control over the global structure of the site.</p>

<p>This component defines the main structure of the site, eg. Header, Content and Footer.</p>
<p>By default, the site object implements the sticky footer pattern. This pattern sticks the footer to the bottom of the browser window when there is not enough content to push it down further.</p>

<hr class="Article-divider">

<h2 id="section:usage"><a href="#section:usages" class="Text--resetLink">Usage</a></h2>

<p>To demonstrate this, click the button below and see how the footer sticks to the bottom of the window.</p>
